A [[wee dram]] is a [[Scottish]] euphemism  for a shot of [[Scotch Whisky]] -- a [[single malt Scotch]], for example from the fragrant far north-east [[North Sea]] coast [[distillery]] of [[Glenmorangie]] or the peaty south west-coast [[Atlantic]] [[Laphroaig]] -- or indeed a dozen or more other famous single malt brands from [[Orkney]] to [[Islay]] -- but more likely a central belt [[Whisky blend]] like [[Famous Grouse]] or [[Black Bottle]]. Given to guests and visitors, it is a typically [[Scottish]] gesture of hospitality, camaderie, national pride and [[Adam Smith]] (spookily, see other famous [[Kirkcaldy]] [[Member of Parliament|MP]], [[New Labour]] Chancellor [[Gordon Brown]]) economics -- hopefully the imbiber won't be able to tell the difference between a single malt and a whisky blend! (around €20, or $40 a 75cl bottle). A [[Whisky Mac]], popular at [[Hogmanay]] along with a rich fruit cake called [[Black Bun]], is equal measures of [[Crabbies Green Ginger]] and Scotch Whisky.